---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Cannabis Zoning & Real Estate | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Finding the right location for your Maine cannabis dispensary. Zoning requirements, lease considerations, and real estate tips."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1582407947304-fd86f028f716?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Cannabis Zoning & Real Estate</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Finding the right location for your Maine cannabis dispensary</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="The Reward of the Perfect Spot" type="passion">
      Finding your physical home in the community is one of the most exciting parts of the journey. When you finally unlock the doors to a space that fits your vision, it becomes the foundation where your passion meets your customers every day. It's not just a lease; it's the start of your legacy in the Maine cannabis scene.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Finding the right location is one of the most critical decisions for your dispensary. Maine municipalities have significant control over where cannabis businesses can operate. Understanding zoning requirements and real estate options is essential before signing a lease.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Zoning Fundamentals</h2>
      <p>Maine municipalities can:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Opt-in or opt-out of allowing cannabis businesses</li>
        <li>Designate specific zones for cannabis operations</li>
        <li>Impose additional local requirements</li>
        <li>Set distance requirements from sensitive locations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Common Zoning Requirements</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Commercial Zoning</strong> - Most dispensaries in commercial or mixed-use zones</li>
        <li><strong>Distance Requirements</strong> - Typically 300-500 ft from schools, churches, playgrounds</li>
        <li><strong>Parking</strong> - Adequate parking required</li>
        <li><strong>Signage</strong> - May have additional restrictions</li>
        <li><strong>Security</strong> - Some towns require security plans</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Finding Properties</h2>
      <h3>Types of Spaces:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Retail Spaces</strong> - Traditional storefronts</li>
        <li><strong>Former Pharmacies</strong> - Good layout, familiar use</li>
        <li><strong>Strip Malls</strong> - Good traffic, shared parking</li>
        <li><strong>Free-Standing Buildings</strong> - More visibility, more cost</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Lease Considerations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Lease Term</strong> - 5+ years recommended</li>
        <li><strong>Build-Out Allowances</strong> - Negotiate tenant improvements</li>
        <li><strong>Exclusivity</strong> - Prevent competitor in same building</li>
        <li><strong>Assignment</strong> - Ability to transfer lease</li>
        <li><strong>Zoning Confirmation</strong> - Verify cannabis-friendly before signing</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Due Diligence</h2>
      <p>Before signing:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Confirm municipality allows cannabis in that zone</li>
        <li>Verify distance from schools, churches</li>
        <li>Check building code compliance</li>
        <li>Review landlord's cannabis policy</li>
        <li>Get estimated build-out costs</li>
        <li>Research traffic patterns and visibility</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Check local zoning before property search</li>
        <li>Verify cannabis allowed in specific zone</li>
        <li>Long-term leases (5+ years) recommended</li>
        <li>Negotiate build-out allowances</li>
        <li>Due diligence is critical before signing</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="external-resources">
      <h2>Further Reading & Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Cannabis regulations are subject to change; always consult with the Maine Office of Cannabis Policy and qualified legal counsel.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .external-resources { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .external-resources ul { list-style: none; padding-left: 0; }
  .external-resources li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
</style>
